        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"815571\">Martin Biehl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Category.20of.20relations.20as.20monoidal.20category/near/491190612\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{Cat}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">Cat</span></span></span></span></span> (seems to be implemented in mathlib4 <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Cat.html\">here</a>)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>We do not have the monoidal structure on <code>Cat</code>, but it would be nice to use the results in the folder <code>Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Products</code>.</p>",
